verbose_text: In rats, the age at puberty onset can be evaluated by the separation of the preputial skin from the glans of the penis [Balanopreputial separation (PPS)] [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] and is triggered by the rise of serum testosterone concentrations in the prepubertal period [XREF_BIBR].
